"This song is exactly like the backing synthesizer phrase of the intro to THE ALFEE's \"Hoshizora no Distance\". Of course, the chords are different, so it's not exactly the same as the song. If you're familiar with The Maze of Galius, you will know that I wanted to create the indescribable solemn atmosphere before the invocation of the great devil.",
"It is the base of all the boss songs. It was made before I knew what it was. It was supposed to be the theme of the boss song, but Samieru-san suggested that we change the song for each boss (I think I would have suggested it even if he hadn't). I suggested that the intro be the same, because I didn't want the music to be inconsistent. However, it was difficult to arrange the introduction because of the chromaticism of the introduction.",
"I think it's very typical of me to end a song with a bass phrase like, \"N-ban-ban-ban! at the end of the song, which is very typical of me.",
"This song is based on a gamelan-style techno song I bought in Bali, and while trying to keep the SCC style tune, I thought it might be possible to make a game music with an ethnic music style, or more like ruins, based on the game content. The SCC version of this song has a terrible mistake. This song has a shuffle beat with bouncing triplets, but when I started making this song, I was making it with a normal beat. When I was working on the second half of the song, I realized, \"Is this arrangement shuffled?\" I realized that it was supposed to be shufflebeat. However, I had to recreate the SCC song data from the temporary MIDI data, which is a pain in the ass...... So, I left it as it was. The MIDI data is shuffle.",
"I imagined an old-fashioned, game-like, store song. But, well, the second half of the phrase is appropriate.",
"I wrote this song when I was running out of ideas. No, I didn't. I was struggling for ideas, so I decided to find a song that I had made a long time ago that I could reuse, so I used a dance piece I made for a play about 8 years ago. It's not suitable for games at all. The part where it's just drums and bass, I don't think I could handle that with just two tones. I was going to change it to another song as soon as I got some subtle comments about it not being game-like, but fortunately I received a rather subtle but complimentary comment about how cool the second half was, so I left it as it was.",
"The tempo of this song matches Sakito's slow and steady attack. I was in charge of arranging the song, but since I liked the tone of the original song, I arranged it as it was without doing anything unnecessary.",
"I was in charge of the empty water source song, but I sealed it off and asked Samieru-san to do it for me. It took me a while to get used to it when it first came out because it had a different groove from the one I had created. That allowed me to arrange it however I wanted. I didn't know the original, but the theme of \"Asghine\" was included in the song, and I almost arranged this part as well. I almost arranged this part, too.",
"I just wanted to do the intro, \"Hee, hee, hee\". That's all! Kyahaha!",
