"I like this song. Or rather, the arrangement. The drums, drums, drums, drums, drums, drums. I was in charge of the arrangement, and I did a lot of the drums and melody. We were originally talking about the speed of this and Ellmac, and both of us had the image of F1 spirit, so we divided the work between the two of us.",
"This is a song that I have been writing since the very beginning, without any particular pyramid in mind. No, no, really. Originally, it was a bit shorter. The latter half of the song was completely missing the part where the tune changes. Samieru-san said it was too short or not enough, didn't he? The songs I made around this time were honest game music for me, and they still had the retro-game feel I struggled to acquire with GR3. Now? Not anymore.",
"I can't spare enough memory space for an 8-bit song like this. I think it took me less than 30 minutes to make this simple song. I think I'm better at creating game-like songs when I take this stance.",
"It was the song that somehow \"grabbed\" me about how to use SSCC. To be more specific, none of the songs I had written up to that point had a tempo as slow as this one. If the tempo is fast, you can cover up a lot of things with a flood of sound, but if it is slow, the good and bad of the phrasing will stand out, and the dullness of the tone will also be noticeable. Therefore, I always add volume increase/decrease or shaking to long notes, and since there are only long notes, I add small phrases in the background to avoid selecting similar sounds in terms of waveforms. I thought about it quite seriously and composed the music. I was praised for this, so I got carried away for a while and got a lot of submissions.",
"A trolley, a fusion like T-SQUARE! The speed of a magic chariot from Romancing SaGa 3! This is what I came up with. The melody line is very fusion-like. I thought, \"If the bass and drums are chopped up, why can't I get a sense of speed? That was my simple idea.",
"A song that was ready early on but kept wandering around without finding a place to settle in. Originally, it was the gate of guidance. We went to the infinite corridor and settled on the twin labyrinth. I decided to use this song as a reference from the MSX Konami game music series so as not to have the same tune in each song and not to spoil the Konami style. The \"tête-à-tête\" part at the beginning and the backing piano phrase. If it's this limited, people won't think it's a pastiche. Mmm-hmm.",
"I made this piece when I was reflecting on my tendency to make complicated music. It's a song about \"Grieg's Castle\" and \"The Sea\" by Moro Shalom. I wanted to make a song that has a pleasant sound that stretches and sways. I am always making messy music, but surprisingly, I also like this kind of music. I feel sorry for the four wise men. They are the lowest of the low.",
"This is another song with twists and turns. I originally imitated the atmosphere of a song that was played on an NHK Silk Road special or something. Even so, I didn't like the subtlety of the melody in the latter half of the song, so I retracted it early on, saying it was just a temporary song, even though I had already created it in the early stages of development. The music for \"The Shrine of the Virgin\" was changed four times, but none of the changes felt right, and when duplex said, \"I like that song, and I had that song in mind when I was making the gate of the lost,\" I said, \"Really? （I thought of that song when I was making the Lost Gate. Of course, I fixed the subtle parts in the latter half of the song.",
"This song also took a lot of work to reach this form. I had to create a sense of wonderment by saying \"I'm lost,\" and I still had to arrange the song for that brave leader. The motif is from the Grasshopper 2 Temple stage, and I created it in the first phase of the arrangement work. At first, I just kept the melody of the guidance and made it creepy. It was too poor, so I made it more like a temple stage tune, and it was also oddly short, so it took this form. I found myself in 3/4 time, and although I tried to keep the phrases of the original song, when I listened to it objectively, I couldn't recognize the original song at all. All that remains is the repetitive pattern after the climax of the song.",
"I was in charge of the MIDI arrangement; I was given a tentative MIDI for the SCC version, and the data was already a rock song with guitars in the backing. I arranged it as a rock song for MIDI without thinking about it, but when I thought about it, I realized it was an ice stage. It was a cheap but effective way to make it more icy by increasing the number of sparkling tones. I was not satisfied with just that, so I also used a \"punch\" tone to express my wish that the giants would hit me on the giant stage.",
"The motif of this one is the same as the Tower of the Goddess. I tried to make a gothic music with harpsichord. I don't feel like I'm trying to make game music at all...maybe it's because the SCC version has a tonal problem, or maybe I didn't make the music to match the tone, but it doesn't sound ideal at all. I was told, \"It's a quiet song, so I thought you wanted me to make it loud for the production! I am now making up for it with the MIDI version.",
"I am in charge of MIDI arrangement. In the late stages of development, Samieru-san told me, \"This song is actually Michael Jackson's Thriller! While I was in charge of the arrangement, Samieru-san was overseas, so I couldn't get confirmation from him. I don't know if this is what he wanted or not, but I added some things that reminded me of a thriller, like the sound of a door closing or a dog barking, to make it sound more like a thriller. It couldn't be helped, could it?",
"I like this one too. The graphics have changed, but the field originally had a mechanical feel to it, so I made it with techno type phrases. the MIDI version changes the bass line and makes the hard distortion guitar sound simple. Hmmm, I like it. It is my favorite SOFT BALLET style arrangement. The rhythm and beat are different from the original, but I think I did a good job of arranging it so that the original is still recognizable. When I was working on this, I was trying to keep myself from messing up the melody line, so I kept the melody simple. The first half is very simple.",
"It is a collection of simple phrases created based on the reflection of \"I wasted a lot of time complicating the melody, and this is not what game music is supposed to be about. But I couldn't hold back, and the drums are playing over and over and over and over. I just can't stop myself from playing something. It's a disease, a disease.",
"I am confident that I have achieved a good balance both musically and as a game song. The motif of this song is not related to the game at all, but it is a hard rock song by MALICE MIZER (after Gackt left the band) with a cembalo playing. I like this kind of tonally elaborate music. It is the sound of \"telorello telorello\" that keeps playing in the background throughout this song. I forced myself to change the chords while keeping the melody as it is. It's fun, isn't it? The fact that it is a game song while thinking about this must be because MANA-sama is a game fanatic. When you get excited while making a song, you can easily create a song without using your head.",
"This is another song that is unique to the game. Surprisingly, it's not hard to create something like this. What is it? Am I suited for it or not?",
"Curry. People say it's BGM for a comical game if it's bad, but I was the one who gave the go-ahead. I had it MIDI-arranged, and I used ethnic percussion instruments to give it a curry flavor. I should have at least made an enemy character with a turban.",
"As you can hear from the MIDI version, I had a lot of interesting motifs and ideas. I layered a lot of creepy sounds on top of each other. The most extreme example is the \"spaceship,\" which is a tone that would never normally be used because it's an ancient spaceship. It's a sound that is made in the back of the ship, like a \"mmmm pishooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo. It's very cheap, even for me.",
