"The synthesizer phrase \"pah, pah, pah, pah,\" sounded in small increments. I was on my way to work when I heard a song from a bowling alley commercial on street corner TV, and it was around the time I was thinking, \"I can't think of Tiamat, but I don't have time\", so I got the phrase. I had only heard it once, so even if I tried to copy it, it wouldn't be the same! I thought. Like Baphomet, this one didn't sound ideal for SCC. I thought I was making a game-like song, but when it got close to 3 minutes long, there was a guitar solo in the latter half of the song, etc. I am not a suitable person for making game music at all. I made the MIDI version as a humiliation, aiming for an ethnic hard arrangement of THE ALFEE's ARCADIA, mixing hard rock with ethnic instruments. What the heck, I'm just going out of my way for my own taste.",
"The song on the ground, or the title track, or the song that should have been written as a stand-alone piece without any back and forth, but before you know it, it's being used as a story for an arrangement. So, I'm not surprised that that title tune, which I made up at random, came back to rock! As I recall, I made an offer to the team: \"A song that will induce a sense of elation, like the song from The Legend of Majojo 3 Shalom that plays during the final battle!\" I remember I made an offer to him.",
"This is another song with no power. It was done quickly. If you don't think about it, it's quick. If you do anything else, it takes a long time and it gets lost.",
